        },
        "rich_text_TTE7Ef": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Misconceptions Paragarph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h4>“Platinum is always more expensive than diamonds.”</h4><p>False. While platinum is rare, diamonds<br/>particularly high-grade stones are far more valuable per unit.</p><h4>“Diamonds are priced by weight like metals.”</h4><p>Incorrect. Diamonds are priced by the 4Cs, not simply by carat weight.</p><h4>“Platinum jewelry costs more purely because of the metal.”</h4><p>Platinum’s density increases cost, but craftsmanship and design also influence final pricing.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bVNEcW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Paragarph2",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>For Budget-Conscious Buyers</h3><ul><li>Choose platinum when the design requires substantial metal weight.<br/></li><li>Choose diamonds cautiously, considering clarity and color to maximize value.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
